Introduction

This project consists of two Python files, headhunter.py and main.py, aimed at extracting job postings related to financial management from the HeadHunter website (hh.ru).
Files

    headhunter.py
        This file contains functions for scraping job postings from the HeadHunter website.
        Functions:
            extract_max_page(): Extracts the maximum number of pages with job listings from the search results.
            extract_hh_jobs(last_page): Extracts job details such as title and company from each job listing on a specified page.

    main.py
        This file serves as the entry point of the project.
        It imports functions from headhunter.py to extract and print job details.

Usage

    Ensure you have Python installed on your system.
    Install the required dependencies using pip install -r requirements.txt.
    Run main.py to extract and display job details.

Dependencies

    requests: For making HTTP requests.
    BeautifulSoup: For parsing HTML content.

Contributing

Contributions to this project are welcome. Feel free to fork the repository, make improvements, and submit pull requests.
